        <headline>Heat Advisory issued July 1 at 12:07AM PDT until July 1 at 9:00PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High temperatures 95 to 100 degrees in the valleys.

* WHERE...Northern Lander and Northern Eureka, Southeastern Elko,
and Southwest Elko Counties.

* WHEN...From 11 AM this morning to 9 PM PDT this evening.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures may cause heat illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
